# Pizza Web App - Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: React 19 + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS + Redux Toolkit
- Backend: NestJS + TypeScript + Prisma ORM + PostgreSQL
- Real-time: Socket.io (WebSockets)
- Auth: JWT (access + refresh tokens), bcrypt for passwords
- Containerization: Docker + docker-compose

## Architecture
- Monorepo: `frontend/` and `backend/` in a single repository
- Frontend: feature-based Redux slices in `src/features/`
- Backend: modular NestJS architecture in `src/modules/`
- API: RESTful, layered separation (controller -> service -> prisma)

## Naming Conventions
- React components: PascalCase (`MenuPage.tsx`, `OrderCard.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useAuth.ts`)
- Redux slices: camelCase (`authSlice.ts`)
- NestJS modules: kebab-case folders, PascalCase classes
- TypeScript files: camelCase for utils/services, PascalCase for components
- Enums: PascalCase name, UPPER_SNAKE_CASE values

## Frontend
- Global state: Redux Toolkit (not Zustand)
- API calls: `services/` layer with axios
- Routing: react-router-dom
- Styling: Tailwind CSS (Shadcn UI to be added later from Figma)
- Pizza creator: prepared folder `features/pizza-creator/` for dnd-kit

## Backend
- Validation: class-validator + class-transformer in DTOs
- Auth: Guards (`JwtAuthGuard`, `RolesGuard`) + decorators (`@Roles()`, `@CurrentUser()`)
- Prisma: migrations via `npx prisma migrate dev`, never edit files in `migrations/` manually
- WebSocket: gateway in the `orders` module
- Passwords: bcrypt, never plain text

## TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled
- Avoid `any` — use types from `types/` (frontend) or DTOs (backend)
- Export types/interfaces from dedicated files

## Database (Prisma)
- Workflow: edit schema -> migrate dev -> generate
- Cost denormalization in orders (`unitCost` in `OrderItemIngredient`)
- Transactions for inventory operations (race conditions)

## User Roles
- CLIENT, EMPLOYEE, ADMIN (RBAC)

## General Rules
- Do not add business logic to skeleton files unless necessary
- Write code in English (variable names, functions, file names)
- Comments and documentation may be in Polish
- Each module/feature should be self-contained
